  "doc_id": "24317",
  "text": "Plasmids were introduced into V. anguillarum VIB15Rif R by conjugation procedures described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, overnight cultures of V. anguillarum and E. coli S17-1 λ-pir were mixed at a ratio of 10:1 in 2.5 ml 10 mM MgSO 4 . The cell mixture was vacuum filtered onto a 0.22-µm-pore-size filter, which was placed on tryptic soy agar (TSA) and allowed to incubate overnight at 25˚C. Following incubation, the cells were harvested and plated on LB agar plates containing 200 µg/ml Rif and 5 µg/ml Cm and allowed to incubate at 25˚C until V. anguillarum colonies were observed.",
